Following up to this. I ran into this issue. It seems like Forge as of the recent nightly builds are escaping strings passed into constructor (and likely other places) in the broadcast JSON. 

Forge v0.2.0 (commit 5b7e4cb)

```solidity
pragma solidity ^0.8.13;

contract Test {

   string public s;

   constructor(string memory _s) {
    s = _s;
   }

}
```

```json
"arguments": [
        "\"HelloWorld\""
 ]
```

This escaping leads to it being encoded as a string:

```json
{
 "arguments": "[\"0x6E5ed6320F977a956fA446EDF43Ab8DaABc274D4\",\"\\OVM_L1CrossDomainMessenger\\\"]"
}
```

Where as Go expects an `[]any` slice/array.

A solution I found for this was to change the Deployer.sol script:

https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/develop/packages/contracts-bedrock/scripts/Deployer.sol#L382

and use `jq` to parse the escaped string as JSON: 

original:
```solidity
     cmd[2] = string.concat(Executables.jq, " -r '.arguments' <<< '", _transaction, "'");
```

new:

```solidity
     cmd[2] = string.concat(Executables.jq, " -r 'try(.arguments|map_values(try(fromjson),.))' <<< '", _transaction, "'");
```

