I think limiting `buffer_layers` may have helped, and made the problem more rare, but was not a water-tight solution. Assuming these other layers (diff between last disk-layer and the root-layer) still end up in the journal, that is still a problem when the journal is dropped, when geth can only handle 128 missing layers.

Out of caution we may want to ask users in the release-notes to consider the full `layers` attribute, not just `buffer_layers`, if present in the shutdown log.
